WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.771 --> 00:00:08.016
Did you know that the castanets used in Spanish folk dancing 
 have been dated back as many as 10,000 years?

00:00:08.147 --> 00:00:11.185
The particular style used today can be tuned for different pitches.

00:00:17.165 --> 00:00:22.094
Within the walls of New York’s Modern Museum of 
 Art, dancers have filled the expansive atrium

00:00:22.094 --> 00:00:25.608
performing a brand new work from French choreographer Boris Charmatz.

00:00:25.650 --> 00:00:30.385
“Musée de la Danse: Three Collective Gestures” was a three-weekend affair,

00:00:30.385 --> 00:00:33.628
each installment adding life and movement to the empty halls.

00:00:33.628 --> 00:00:38.261
With 25 simple, repetitive movements set in unique patterns on the 24 dancers,

00:00:38.261 --> 00:00:43.180
Charmatz’s choreography created interesting and unexpected synchronous moments.

00:00:43.180 --> 00:00:47.415
How awesome to see the museum involving art 
 that can’t be hung in a gallery!

00:00:47.953 --> 00:00:55.019
I know summer is over, but as temperatures drop, Tim 
 Milgrams latest is sure to warm your dancin' soul.

00:00:55.019 --> 00:01:00.257
Performed and choreographed by Kento Mori, Mona Berntsen, Hefa Tuita and Randi Kemper.

00:01:00.257 --> 00:01:05.521
"Jammin" takes you from the streets to the 
 beach with a unique blend of styles.

00:01:05.521 --> 00:01:09.243
It's colorful, it's personality and for me, it's different.  Check it out…

