Former So You Think You Can Dance finalist Cole 
 Horibe is bringing his martial arts experience

00:01:53.164 --> 00:01:57.100
to David Henry Hwang’s new off-Broadway show, Kung Fu.

00:01:57.104 --> 00:02:03.040
Landing the lead role of Bruce Lee, Cole with be reunited 
 with another familiar So You Think You Can Dance face,

00:02:03.036 --> 00:02:06.260
as Sonya Tayeh has been selected to choreograph the show.

00:02:06.263 --> 00:02:12.270
This ought to be a kick-ass production! Which by 
 the way is opening next February 2014…

00:02:12.693 --> 00:02:18.010
It’s part of the job as a dancer to have the 
 willingness to try anything the choreographer asks of you, right?

00:02:18.007 --> 00:02:22.300
Marie Chouinard really challenged her dancers with her newest work, “Gymnopedies”,

00:02:22.302 --> 00:02:25.320
by making them learn to play the music they would be dancing to!

00:02:25.323 --> 00:02:27.930
Considering it “choreography for the fingers”,

00:02:27.927 --> 00:02:32.560
Chouinard had each dancer learn to play one of the 
 three piano pieces being used for the work.

00:02:32.558 --> 00:02:35.960
None of them had any prior piano experience, but with enough practice

00:02:35.962 --> 00:02:40.070
they managed to play their own music in performance. Pretty impressive!

